               <msContents class="#multipleWorks">
                  <summary>The Hidden Words (Kalimát-i-Maknúna) of Bahá'u'lláh, in both their
                     Persian and Arabic portions, together with three Epistles addressed to the
                     Zoroastrian community. Browne's initial enquiry concerned passages quoted from
                     a "Hidden Book of Fáṭima" in the Epistle to the King of Persia; what eventually
                     reached him under this press-mark was the general Hidden Words together with
                     the Zoroastrian epistles. Sent as the companion to <ref
                        target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_602">F. 32 (BBA.
                        3)</ref>, forwarded in the meantime while this manuscript was being
                     prepared.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="F_33-item1" n="1">
                     <locus from="1b" to="37a">ff. 1b-37a</locus>
                     <author key="person_88702713" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/88702713/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Baháʼuʼlláh,
                           1817-1892</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">بهاء الله</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_2578">Kalimāt-i mankūnah-ʼi
                        fāṭimīyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_2578">كلمات منكونۀ فاطميه</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="work_2578">Hidden Words</title>
                     <note>Persian portion (ff. 1a-31a): over 80 short clauses, each opening with a
                        poetic invocation (e.g. "O SON OF..."); the invocations are written in red.
                        Browne quotes the opening clause and the invocations of the following nine
                        clauses, and the final clause (f. 31a) in full. Four of the passages cited
                        from this work in the Epistle to the King of Persia are located by Browne to
                        specific folios (ff. 8b, 8b, 9a, 10a).</note>
                     <note>Arabic portion (ff. 33a-36b): 18 short clauses, similar in form to the
                        Persian portion, separated from it by four blank pages (ff. 31b-32b).</note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa" cert="low" resp="#ocr-draft">بنام گوینده توانا ای صاحبان
                        هوش و گوش اول سروش دوست اینست ای بلبل معنوی جز در گلبن معانی جای
                        مگزین...</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa" cert="low" resp="#ocr-draft">... ای عباد جواهر کلمات
                        بدیعه که ورای پرده‌های بیان مستور و مکنون بود... (f. 31a)</explicit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>
                           <ref target="https://cudl.lib.cam.ac.uk/view/PR-A-00233-00004/95"
                              >p.69</ref>
                        </bibl>
                        <bibl>See sub classmark <idno>BBA. 4</idno> in Browne's "Catalogue and
                           Description of 27 Bābī Manuscripts (Continuation)", in Journal of the
                           Royal Asiatic Society of Great Britain and Ireland (Oct., 1892):
                           637-710.</bibl>
                        <bibl type="text-relations"/>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian, Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="F_33-item2" n="2">
                     <locus from="37a" to="41b">ff. 37a-41b</locus>
                     <author key="person_88702713" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/88702713/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Baháʼuʼlláh,
                           1817-1892</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">بهاء الله</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="work_2579">Three letters addressed to the
                        Zoroastrians</title>
                     <note>Three short Epistles, the first (f. 37a) quoted in full by Browne; the
                        second (ff. 37b-39b) and third (ff. 39b-41b, concluding the manuscript)
                        given only in incipit.</note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa" cert="low" resp="#ocr-draft">این سه لوح مبارک از الواحی
                        است که خطاب به زرتشتیان... هو المقصود مشوش مباشید در فکر اصلاح عالم و تهذیب
                        امم باشید...</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa" defective="true"/>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>
                           <ref target="https://cudl.lib.cam.ac.uk/view/PR-A-00233-00004/95"
                              >p.69</ref>
                        </bibl>
                        <bibl>See sub classmark <idno>BBA. 4</idno> in Browne's "Catalogue and
                           Description of 27 Bābī Manuscripts (Continuation)", in Journal of the
                           Royal Asiatic Society of Great Britain and Ireland (Oct., 1892):
                           637-710.</bibl>
                        <bibl type="text-relations"/>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
